# Investor governance lane — positioning lock (v1)

| Field | Value |
|-------|--------|
| Status | LOCKED |
| Branch context | `cursor/platform-blueprint-37f0` |
| Parent | [PLATFORM_BLUEPRINT.md](../../PLATFORM_BLUEPRINT.md) §4.2 Copilot wedge, §11 Trust Ledger |

## Wedge sentence (buy-side)

For VCs and acquirers: Noetfield is **independent decision-evidence diligence** for Microsoft Copilot and agentic operational intent — shadow evaluate orientation, signed Trust Ledger samples, and board-export artifacts so you can underwrite governance risk before term sheet, not after a front-page incident.

## Two-lane diligence model

| Lane | Question | Noetfield role |
|------|----------|----------------|
| **Technical AI diligence** | Is the AI real, scalable, and owned? | **Out of scope** — refer to technical DD specialists |
| **Governance / human-architecture** | Can the target prove oversight, decision authority, and regulatory defensibility? | **In scope** — Trust Brief + Trust Ledger samples + procurement pack |

## SKU mapping (no fourth product)

| Market label | Locked SKU | Intake vector |
|--------------|------------|---------------|
| Investor Shadow Governance Brief | **Trust Brief** (6 weeks) | `?vector=investor-diligence` |
| Copilot rollout evidence pack | **Copilot Readiness Pack** | existing copilot vectors |
| FRFI shadow simulation | **Bank pilot** (Gate) | `gate/procurement` |

Price bands in sales conversations ($15k–$35k) map to **Trust Brief tier selection** — not a new catalog SKU.

## What we cover (~6/18 checklist items)

1. AI system inventory orientation (materiality map via Trust Brief)
2. Human review for high-stakes decisions (TLE approval chain samples)
3. Exportable go/no-go audit trail (Trust Ledger samples + procurement pack)
4. EU AI Act / NIST orientation (playbook + diligence docs — orientation only)
5. Incident response orientation (evaluate → record → export spine)
6. Vendor/subprocessor posture (metadata-only evidence fence)

## What we do not claim

- EU AI Act, SOC 2, or ISO **certification**
- Full 18-item VC checklist coverage
- Technical AI DD (model benchmarks, code review, valuation, moat)
- Training-data provenance or bias testing logs (legal / model-risk specialists)
- Custody, payments, MSB execution

## Partner referral matrix (internal — no vendor names on www)

| Gap | Refer to |
|-----|----------|
| Model architecture, benchmarks, cost-to-fix (tech) | Technical AI DD boutique |
| Training data IP, output ownership | Legal counsel + tech DD |
| Liability allocation in term sheet | Transaction counsel |
| Purview/DLP readiness only | MSP / SI partner |

